            <p  style="text-decoration:none; color:#398AC9;font-style: italic;">
                In the following article, we are going to share with you the best cruise options for single adventurers in Galapagos.
                To a solo traveler it may look challenging to visit the Galapagos, but there are some cruises that offer single cabins with no single supplement.

            </p>

            <p>

                Vacationing on your own is an eye-opening experience that allows you to meet all different kinds of people, travel at your will, and decide when and where you want to go. If you have the chance to do it one day, we highly recommend it. However, for those on a budget, the thrill of traveling solo in Galapagos can sometimes be thwarted by the fact that you may find yourself paying more for lodgings and tours.

            </p>



            <p id="TravelOptions">
                When planning to travel alone to the Galapagos, you may encounter the term <b> ‘SINGLE SUPPLEMENT’:</b>
            </p>


            <p>
                <h2 style="color:black; text-align:left">
                    <b>
                        What does the term ‘single supplement’ really mean?
                    </b>
                </h2>
            </p>


            <p>
                Quite often, people traveling alone or those who wish to occupy single accommodation designed for two or
                more people are required to pay a single supplement,
                as prices per person are always calculated based on double occupancy (and in some cases triple).
                Don't let this stop you, because thankfully some <b>
                    cruise
                    options in Galapagos are designed exclusively for solo travelers
                </b>.
                Being a single traveler in the Galapagos doesn't have to be as expensive as you might have initially thought.
            </p>
            <p>
                <h2 style="color:black; text-align:left">
                    <b>
                        More options for solo travel on a Galapagos cruise

                    </b>
                </h2>
            </p>


            <p>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 15px;">
                    <li>
                        <b>If you can share a booth</b>, tour agencies can pair you with another traveler only to share a
                        room and reduce costs, but not always. Sometimes, a cruise doesn´t
                        filled up all the spaces, so you may be lucky to enjoy the cabin just for yourself.
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <b>  Ask a travel expert</b> to find a Galapagos cruise for you that offers   <b>  single cabins that don't require single supplement.</b>
                    </li>


                </ul>

            </p>


            <p>
                <h2 style="color:black; text-align:left">
                    <b>
                        Galapagos Cruises for solo travelers

                    </b>
                </h2>


            </p>


